An 18-year-old trainee nurse died on a hen party when a lorry driver smashed into their coach which was travelling at just 5mph on a motorway, a court has heard.

Bethany Jones was with a group of 20 women on their way to Liverpool when their coach was hit on the M62 in West Yorkshire by an articulated vehicle.

Lorry driver Kevin Ollerhead, 45, from Merseyside, denies causing death by dangerous driving and went on trial today at Leeds Crown Court.

