'He was driving a large articulated truck in a lane of traffic on a motorway and the standard of care he demonstrated was far below someone in his position.

'He can't have been paying attention and taking steps to avoid a collision by simply driving into the rear of the coach without breaking.

'The journey in fact ended abruptly in a tragic collision close to junction 32 on the M62.'

The coach driver, James Johnson, 64, from Bradford, pleaded guilty to causing Miss Jones's death by dangerous driving at an earlier hearing, the jury heard.

His 24-seat Mercedes minibus began showing signs of mechanical error just minutes into the hen party journey on April 26 last year.

